# Testing and verification — terminal use

## Two agent gate tiers

| Tier | When | Command |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Dev scoped** (default) | Ordinary substantive edits done | [dev-scoped-verify.mdc](dev-scoped-verify.mdc) + [fantasia-dev-scoped-verify](../skills/fantasia-dev-scoped-verify/SKILL.md) |
| **Full quality gate** | Final cleanup, **`git commit`**, user asks full verify/ensure | **`yarn testbatch:verify`** |

## Full quality gate

ESLint (repo), TypeScript, Stylelint, Vitest + coverage (**95%** / **80%** / **100%** / **95%** **per instrumented file** via **`thresholds.perFile: true`**: **`src-electron`**; **`helpers/**/*.ts`** **`unit-helpers`** (**`helpers/playwrightHelpers_*`** excluded); scoped **`i18n/`** (**`unit-i18n`**); renderer **`src`** **`.ts`** (**`unit-src-renderer`**); **`.ts`** and **`.vue`** under **`src/components`**, **`src/layouts`**, **`src/pages`** (**`unit-components`**) — **one** terminal. Prefer **`yarn testbatch:verify`** (stops first failure):

`yarn testbatch:verify`

**Yarn 1.x**: do **not** use `yarn check` — validates dependency tree, not this script.

Equivalent: `yarn lint:eslint && yarn lint:typescript && yarn lint:stylelint && yarn test:coverage:verify`

**Run full gate when:**

- [final-cleanup.mdc](final-cleanup.mdc) / [fantasia-final-cleanup](../skills/fantasia-final-cleanup/SKILL.md)
- User explicitly requests **`yarn testbatch:verify`**, full verify, full gate, **`testbatch:ensure:*`**
- **`git commit`** ([git-conventional-commits.mdc](git-conventional-commits.mdc)) — changelog-only exception below

**Do not** run full gate after every ordinary edit batch — use dev scoped gate instead.

## End of code edits (agents) — default

Substantive source edits in a turn → **last verification** before done summary:

1. **Dev scoped gate** — one terminal ([dev-scoped-verify.mdc](dev-scoped-verify.mdc)): eslint touched paths, **`yarn lint:typescript`**, stylelint touched styles, **`yarn vitest run`** connected specs only.
2. Dev Electron compile smoke (**20s**; kill agent-spawned dev after pass) — second terminal, [dev-electron-compile-check.mdc](dev-electron-compile-check.mdc).

- **Any edit after step 1 passed** → step 1 **invalid**; re-run on current tree.
- **Do not** report “done” / “shipped” / “fixed” without Shell scoped gate on final tree.
- **Do not** substitute scoped gate for full verify before **commit** or **final cleanup**.

**Beyond scoped gate:** connected **Playwright** component + **E2E** per [fantasia-testing](../skills/fantasia-testing/SKILL.md). Full gate does **not** include those.

**Changelog-only exception** (rare): commit **only** **`i18n/*/documents/changeLog.md`** **and** full **`yarn testbatch:verify`** already passed after latest substantive edits with **no** other uncommitted changes → may skip gate before that commit. **Default**: changelog in **same commit** as substantive work. **Uncertain** → run full gate.

**Debug** specific failing step → run command alone until pass; then scoped gate (or full gate if committing / final cleanup).

By default do not chain scoped/full gate with `yarn quasar:build:electron`, Playwright, or Storybook in one shell line.

## Full-suite gates (`testbatch:ensure:nochange` / `testbatch:ensure:change`)

Explicit full project gate in one command (user/manual or explicit agent request):

- **`yarn testbatch:ensure:nochange`** — `testbatch:verify`, **`yarn quasar:build:electron:summarized`** (Quasar/electron-builder output; success one line; failure full log — default **`test-results/quasar-build-electron-last.log`**, gitignored with **`test-results/`**), Playwright component + E2E, **`yarn test:storybook:smoke`**, **`yarn test:storybook:visual`** (committed VRT snapshots; fails on drift). **`yarn test:storybook:visual`** also fails when story iframe has neither element children under **`#storybook-root`** nor **`#root`** nor visible portaled dialog/menu chrome after waiter (mount ids inspected separately — not only first **`querySelector('#storybook-root, #root')`**) unless **`tags: ['skip-visual-render-check']`** or **id** in **`EXCLUDED_STORY_IDS`** in **`.storybook-workspace/visual-tests/storybook.visual.playwright.test.ts`**. **`yarn test:storybook:visual`** fails only on **GitHub** **`windows-latest`** with **`toHaveScreenshot`** pixel counts just above **`maxDiffPixels`** → **README** **Storybook visual baseline policy** (**`maxDiffPixels`** = whole-image differing-pixel cap, not width).
- **`yarn testbatch:ensure:change`** — same through E2E + smoke, then **`yarn test:storybook:visual:update`** for intentional UI baseline refresh. Use only when UI changes approved + commit updated snapshots.

Intentional exception to isolation rule. **Do not** run **`testbatch:ensure:change`** in CI or validate unchanged baseline.

Default **GitHub Actions** **Verify** (`.github/workflows/verify.yml`) runs **`yarn testbatch:verify`** only — not Storybook smoke/visual, Electron production build, Playwright component/E2E. Run **`yarn test:storybook:visual`** / **`yarn testbatch:ensure:nochange`** locally for VRT.

## Everything else — one command per terminal

Each in **own** terminal (no chain with scoped/full gate) unless **`yarn testbatch:ensure:nochange`** or **`yarn testbatch:ensure:change`**:

- `yarn quasar:build:electron` (full build log; streaming output)
- `yarn test:components`
- `yarn test:e2e`
- `yarn test:storybook:smoke`
- `yarn test:storybook:visual` / `yarn test:storybook:visual:update` (and other `test:storybook:visual*` variants)

Isolated logs → easier failure triage.

**Playwright Electron `userData`:** Component/E2E set `TEST_ENV`; main uses **`%APPDATA%/<package.json name>/playwright-user-data`** (repo: **`Roaming\fantasia-archive\playwright-user-data`**), **not** **`fantasia-archive-dev`**. Specs: **`test.describe.serial`**; each group **`test.beforeAll`** **`await`**s **`launchFaPlaywrightComponentHarnessWindow`** / **`launchFaPlaywrightE2eAppWindow`**, which run **`resetFaPlaywrightIsolatedUserData()`** from **`helpers/playwrightHelpers_universal/playwrightUserDataReset.ts`** before **`electron.launch`**. See **`src-electron/mainScripts/appIdentity/appIdentity_manager.ts`**, **`playwrightIsolatedUserDataDirName.ts`**, [playwright-tests.mdc](playwright-tests.mdc).

**Playwright `keyboard.press` (cross-OS keybinds):** Component/E2E driving global shortcuts or keybind capture must match app **primary** (Command macOS, Control Windows/Linux) vs **literal Control** in saved overrides. **`helpers/playwrightHelpers_universal/faPlaywrightKeyboardChords.ts`** + **Keyboard strings** in [playwright-tests.mdc](playwright-tests.mdc); [fantasia-testing](../skills/fantasia-testing/SKILL.md) **Playwright keyboard.press and app keybinds**.

## Reporting

Substantive work: end with scoped gate result (steps + vitest paths) or full verify when applicable — [dev-electron-compile-check.mdc](dev-electron-compile-check.mdc).
